{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix scheduling priority inversion in DL config REL12 DLSCH PDU packing\n\n### Summary\nThere is a scheduling priority inversion where lower-priority traffic is served before higher-priority downstream of function pack_dl_config_dlsch_pdu_rel12_value(). When calling pack_dl_config_dlsch_pdu_rel12_value() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in pack_dl_config_dlsch_pdu_rel12_value or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\nThe root cause was that the n_dl_harq field in the REL12 DLSCH PDU structure could be set to 0, which is an invalid value according to 3GPP specifications. This invalid value caused downstream scheduling logic to incorrectly prioritize the traffic, leading to priority inversion where lower-priority traffic was served before higher-priority traffic.\n\nThe fix ensures that n_dl_harq is never 0 by setting it to a minimum value of 1 when the original value is 0. This prevents the invalid configuration that was causing the scheduling priority inversion.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Added validation in pack_dl_config_dlsch_pdu_rel12_value() to ensure n_dl_harq is never 0, setting it to 1 as a minimum valid value.\n"
}